{
  "message": "fix(templates): XSS escape agent name in retire dialog, expand Tailwind color palettes, add Alpine.js Collapse plugin\n\nSecurity fix in mail_project.html: the retire-agent confirmation\ndialog's inline onclick handler now applies | forceescape after\n| tojson when interpolating the agent name, preventing potential\ncross-site scripting if an agent name contains characters that could\nbreak out of the HTML attribute context (tojson alone does not escape\nHTML entities within attributes).\n\nFrontend enhancements in base.html:\n- Expanded success, warning, and danger color scales from 50/500/600\n  shades to full 50-950 ranges (100-900 plus 950) for finer-grained\n  color usage across the UI\n- Added Alpine.js Collapse plugin script tag before Alpine.js core\n  (required load order) to enable smooth expand/collapse animations\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
